caption: Good food. Ready when promised.

Food was good, ordered the jerk lamb chops. They were very flavorful, crab rolls were okay, nothing fancy, & I was hoping the mac n cheese would've been a little more flavorful & a little bigger portion. I give them 3.5 stars

Great food, the only thing I didnt like was parking when I went to pick up the food I had to park on the road. So if you doing delivery get there at the time they tell you your food will be ready so to avoid parking violation. Apart from this the food was worth the violation. The surf and turf fries, crab cake egg rolls had me wanting to drive back to the restaurant for some more.

My drive was well worth it!!!! I drove almost 2 hours to go eat their food and I can drive another 2 hours to come back again. The food was fire!!!!!!!! The Salmon, lamb chops, wings and the CRAB cakes are all out of this world! If I lived close to this restaurant I would probably be eating there 8 times a week, yes 8 days in a 7 day week!!!!!!!!! The surf 'n' turf was a hit too coz the sauce was spicy some, the lamp chops are juicy and the shrimp are really colossal huge! I'd be glad to come back here and eat their food again.
Crab Cakes Egg Rolls are Amazing!!
All of the food is delicious. When you go in to pick up your food the people that greet you at the door have a smile in their voice tone. It is always a pleasurable experience

Amazingly DELICIOUS... the lamb chops were sooo juicy and tender seasoned to perfection. The colossal shrimp perfect and the Asiago mashed potatoes 💣 and I absolutely loved the online ordering very easy to navigate.

I visited my friend in Maryland and she has been wanting to try this place. We had the fried lobster, jerk lamb chops and crab egg rolls. I have been dreaming about them ever since. Every time I go back I will have to go here! We had to order and pick up. Food was fresh and fast.
Its was ok mac and cheese could have better hotter and better and the mash could use some gravy fr

The food was great! I ordered the crab eggs rolls and the warhead shrimp. I will definitely be going back. Check this place out, you will not be disappointed! You place your orders online and they send you a text when your food is ready. Will definitely be going back.
The crab egg roll are the best

Good service.  My take out order was ready on time.  I tried the crab cake eggrolls and they were great.  Sauces were good too.  Keep in mind when getting it to go, the eggrolls lose some of the crispness from the steam.
Food was great quality was not enough for what what I got

Wasn’t impressed. For the price the portions were very small.  I got the honey glazed lamb chops, Mac and cheese and kale.  The lamb chops weren’t flavorful, the Mac and cheese was bland and the kale was salty.  I wouldn’t recommend.
Food taste good but they give me mac n cheese in small bowl for 7 dollars. It was only 4 spoons and the container wasn't even full

Honestly I’m just so disappointed, I drove over an hour for some food and it just looked crazy. For being a cook and selling food myself the presentation was horrible. Makes you not want to eat it! The Asiago mashed potatoes tasted old. I expect my first time to be better. For this place to be hyped up I’m really disappointed, Especially on a Tuesday!

Absolutely delicious and worth every penny! Ordered a spread that included a crab cake, lobster, lamb, Mac and cheese and greens. The greens might have possibly been the most delicious I have ever had. The crab cake egg rolls were unfortunately sold out but I’ll definitely be back and can’t wait to try them!
The food was AWESOME!!!! We really loved the crab cake egg rolls!!!!

Yummmmmmmmmy!! We got the warhead shrimp and crab cake egg rolls for some late night eats on a Friday. They were BUSY and the employees were doing a great job at getting all the orders out pandemic-style. The food was the ultimate comfort food and I can’t stop thinking about it one day later. Next, I really want to try the lamb chops and I’m looking forward to the day when we can dine in!
Those crab egg rolls were fantastic! I didn't expect it to live up to the hype but it certainly did.
The crab eggrolls and warhead shrimp were so good, the sauce was everything. Honestly everything was good including the stuffed salmon. I thought the lamb lollipops were ok...

Food was dope.  Portion sizes not the best.  Comparing them to other local places like Taste This and others...  The portion size are definitely lacking. I paid $7 for Mac N Cheese and it should've been priced at $4-5 for small and then large should've been the 7. Crabcake was broken apart; almost as if someone had took half of it. For the most part, the food was pretty good but presentation, portion sizes, and heat of the food were all lacking here and the signage on the building needs to be larger and in the front for first time customers.  I'd recommend this for a try but wouldn't be a go to place for me like others unless I give it another try.
Good food

This is my favorite place to visit! I’ve had the jerk lamb chops, crab cake egg rolls, asparagus and mac and cheese and loved them all, but I HIGHLY recommend the warhead shrimp and honey glazed stuffed salmon.
The food was amazing
Loved it

I was soooo excited to try Papicuisine and finally placed an order last night 2-21-21. I ordered the crabcakes eggrolls, crabcakes with lamb chops meal, lamb chops meal, and the warhead shrimp. The service and the overall process of ordering went great.  So this review is to first assure the buyer that papicuisine knows what to do with food. For the most part the flavor profile is there. Second is to let the owner know that you are not delivering a consistent product.  The crab cake was delicious and full of chunks of crabmeat and flavor.  The crabcakes eggrolls would have been perfect but were VERY SALTY. I couldnt eat them after one bite.  The lamb chop flavor profile was ON POINT delicious but they were over cooked and I have never in my life seen chops that small.  To be clear, they were so small that I would have needed about 10 chops to make up one portion of meat.  The mac-n-cheese was dry and flavorless but with a little finesse could be much better  The kale was good to me but it does have a twangy/sweet flavor but I liked it  The shrimp were very good also.  Overall I think that once the actual restaurant opens for in person dining I will try them again. I know they have the potential to be great and I want to be there for to taste the greatness.

My order was for 2:55 p.m I received an email at 2:40 p.m. that my food was ready for pick up. When I arrived it still wasn't ready. My food wasn't hot and I thought it would be being as though I still had to wait to get it. We always go to places based on reviews and just looking to try something knew. However, for me and my husband we weren't impressed at all. The food was blandly seasoned so we're still wondering what's all the hype about. We tried it like we said we would but it wasn't anything to write home about for us. We live an hour away from this location by the way,so we traveled to see what it was about.Hopefully others will enjoy when they visit.
Crab cake eggrolls are delicious 😋
Definitely not worth the price...,photos on social media didn’t match the food...false advertisement

So today is Valentines Day. I preordered a $116 dollars worth of food early yesterday. I arrived to chaos at my scheduled pick up time. My food wasn’t ready. I was asked to wait 20 minutes. 20 minutes later still no food. It took another 20 minutes for them to tell myself and several other customers, they were out of lamb. In truth they were out of everything. So no Valentines Day meal for us despite doing our due diligence and ordering a day ahead. Such a waste of time.
Drove all the way from NY to place an order... Nice staff & food was superb.

My wife & I had seen this restaurant on Instagram before covid 19 hit & then fought tooth & nail to get a reservation. No one ever answers the phones there & you can’t leave special instructions when making the reservation.  My wife finally got a reservation and we drove the 3 hours from NY for a date night. When we got there, we were a little shocked because we were apparently overdressed we thought we were going somewhere with some kind of up scale ambience and it was the opposite of that. Very small & quaint which I’m usually a fan of because it’s more intimate interactions much like NY but they weren’t covid 19 compliant at all. It didn’t much feel like the place for a date night but the place you go after dinner for a night cap. There were flies all over the establishment, table was wobbly, music was loud and explicit like a dive bar  The FOOD was AMAZING which is why they are even getting 2 stars from me. I got the stuffed lobster and jerk lamb chops and crab cake egg rolls and my wife got the stuffed salmon and warhead shrimp. As a foodie especially out of NY, it’s GOOD food  Our waitress on the other hand who I think may have been amber or Ashley (she had locs) was unquestionably rude to my wife when she inquired about items on the menu, and she also appeared to be having a separate conversation on her headphones while taking our orders which was really odd. We later tried to grab her attention but she was standing at the bar taking shots with other customers so my wife attempted to get up to grab her attention & she came running over once she seen my wife walking over. I think she sensed our frustrations because she instantly became apologetic and brought us drinks on the house that we declined because our parking was almost up and just asked for our check...... someone at the bar asked her were we upset and she goes “I get my tip regardless” as If we didn’t matter as patrons. I’m a native New Yorker and we are living in pandemic times & I am in support of the auto gratuity on service industry tabs  but with this being my experience I’m sorry my wife and I got so overly dressed , I’m sorry I drove the 3 hours & im sorry I’ll never dine in here again. avoid the flies, attitude & automatic gratuity and just DoorDash the takeout

The food was good. I ordered carry out it was ready when I arrived. I want to try the pasta that I see getting posted on line but i don't see them on the menu which is frustrating.... how can I try a delicious looking pasta dish?
The crabcake egg rolls are the best I ever had, there are 2 different house made dipping sauces which are fantastic. The weekends are their most busiest of times but the wait is well worth it.
Jerk lamb chops and salmon delicious as well as the crab cake egg rolls.
Poor customer service and very rude and no menus in store
Great food
Terrible customer service and food is not that good.

This food is amaaaaaazing!!!!!!! Great service. The wings are delicious, the lobster is delicious. Make sure if you get the lobster you take your time because it takes a bit longer to cook. I recommend this place for sure. A bit pricey to be aware but it’s worth it!!! 😍😍
Amazing!
Papi's has delicious food, no matter what I order I am not disappointed. And the margarita flavors are very varied and fun to choose from.
Food was ok....certain parts of my order was cold
HONEYYYYYYYY..... they never disappoint , I love it here the best food in Balitmore. Nicely put together and SO GOOD. I promise you. Go get ya PAPI’s🥰😘

Worth every penny! I should have taken a pic prior to digging in, but my stomach was screaming “Feed Me, Now”, and I must admit I was overwhelmingly surprised with the flavor, portion sizes, customer service, and overall take out experience. This was definitely worth it; thanks Papi Cuisine for not disappointing my stomach!!!!!
Came here for my mom's birthday, and we were not disappointed. I had the salmon and the crab egg roll, both were very good. Will definitely return for the dine in experience once allowed.
Excellent customer service. The lady that was taking orders today around 1:30pm was really on point with everyone's orders. Thank you
This time I ordered the stuff crab eggrolls and they were mouth watering delicious.

This was so delicious. The lamb was fire and the egg rolls were the truth. The honey jerk sauce from the lamb taste so delicious with everything. Even dipping the crab roll in it was bomb. The salmon was stuffed with jumbo Maryland crab and was so tender and juicy.
I had the Crab cake Egg rolls, very good! Take out order was ready quickly.

So I have wanted to try Papi Cuisine for months.  Finally I decided to treat myself for my birthday.   Holy cow the Crabcake Eggroll!! Crisy flaky,shell, moist,  sumptuous lump crab!!!  The dips!!!  I am going to go back tomorrow. I must try the entire menu.  Baltimore peeps, the crabcake just got an upgrade
Food was great, I really love it!
Food took over 2 hrs , owner is very rude . Service is terrible my order was canceled after waiting 2hrs for crab egg rolls and warhead shrimp. Will never go back ever !!!!
I randomly saw a tik tok video this morning of this place and had to try the crab egg rolls... they are fire. For the YT people, they are delicious. Get some. I drove an hour just to try them.
Excellent would highly recommend
Never again.....missing 2 sides. Who wants to drive back 35 mins to get something that’s offered with the meal??????
Always great!!!
So good! Go to place when i am in the area! 10/10

Over the past year this place has taken the Baltimore Area by storm. With excellent service paired with amazing staff is begs for a return. And if that wasn’t enough the food blows me away everytime. Yes the egg rolls are that great. Yes the stuffed salmon is that epic.
Everything i have had from there is the bomb.com. Always flavorful and always fresh. I love their food.

Let me just say,, I drove from Philadelphia to Baltimore and the drive was worth it, crab cake little to no filler all crabmeat, mac and cheese very rich, a few different cheeses, the lump crabmeat egg rolls very delicious,, I was truly satisfied,, I 100%recommended visiting if ever in Baltimore,,, online ordering also

Both visits and the food was very tasty. Flavor overload for sure! Staff has always been friendly and accommodating, if possible. Decent order service style setup. Highly recommend this place to anyone ,especially seafood!
Great service, Full of Flavor and Quality food. SOOOO GOOOD

Saw a thread about this restaurant on Twitter by (Baltimore Food Blogger) and I was so excited that I made sure I stopped by after work. This is so worth the price($20) for the four crab cake rolls. It is so savory and mouth watering!!🥰 customer service is A1 and the food is right up after you order.  If you are in the downtown. Baltimore area, definitely a spot to check out.

My wife and I love this food. The crab egg rolls are fantastic, a bit pricey but worth it. Parking is a little tricky but the food is so good that it is worth the effort of parking. Food is a must have/try.
Amazing food and service! Colossal crabcake eggrolls are now a must for anyone in Baltimore.

Food was overall good. I purchased the honey salmon and the jerk lamb with crabcake. Sides were kale, asiago mashed potatoes, and mac n cheese. The portions weren't bad and most everything had a nice flavor. The kale was very vinegary though and was the only thing I didn't really like. My only gripe is the price.  A little overpriced for what you get. It wasn't some new take on old favorites which could validate a few extra bucks.
100% the best! Great atmosphere and customer service! I can’t wait to see what they have in store for the future!
Great food and good service 👌

I ordered the crab cakes, warhead shrimp, lambchops, and stuffed salmon with sides as a to-go order. Overall, I was highly disappointed. HIGHLY DISAPPOINTED. The lambchops were severely overcooked. The meat was tough and the flavor was unpleasant. The stuffed salmon looked nothing like the IG pics. It was dry and hard. We couldn't even eat it. The crab inside didn't taste good either. I must say that the crab cake was decent and the warhead shrimp was the best item (nice size and flavor). The mac and cheese was stiff and left much to be desired. Again, we couldn't eat it. Lastly, 2 of my sides were missing...I did not receive them. That shows a lack of attention to detail. The ordering process was smooth and timely though. Overall, I was very excited to try this place but will not be returning. My at-home dinner date was a bust. We were left hungry and unsatisfied after spending $100.
Staff was attentive and nice.. Crab cake egg rolls were good. My husband really liked his lamb chops.
Soooo good! It was fresh, hot and flavorful!🤤 Definitely going back soon.
My only disappointment was they were sold out of the colossal crabcake egg rolls, but that just gives me a reason to come back! 😉😋
Great food love the atmosphere.
This place was Amazing! The food was second to non! I need this in my life on a monthly basis!!
The food and drinks are amazing here. Traveled from NYC to try crab egg rolls 😋. Pineapple Margarita was strong and delicious. Definitely coming back soon.

The food is excellent!! I had the crab egg rolls, crab stuffed salmon, Mac n cheese, asparagus and kale. The kale had too much vinegar to my taste. However everything else was delish!!  Can’t wait until they open up their other location which will help with seating. This location is small and intimate which is why the long wait for a reservation. But worth the wait to get in!! Yummm

I ordered online and picked it up from the store. My only complaint is that I tried to get into contact with them about my order because I have a shellfish allergy. I just wanted to notify them to make sure my food wasn't cooked near or with any shellfish. There wasn't a place to write notes on the order. They didn't pick up when I called and no one responded when I wrote them on IG. When I arrived I was able to let them know, after I already paid. Thankfully it wasn't made near it. The jerk lambs were tasty. The Mac n cheese was good. I didn't like the mashed potatoes.

Love the food!!! I had the crab cake meal and the crab egg rolls!! Soooo good, the meals come with 3 sides and I could not even eat it all!! The crab egg rolls are a must as an appetizer!! Already booked twice to return!

Had a wonderful crab cake fest here with my cousins ! Randomly got in the car and drove from NYC. Solid menu tried the Crab Cake Eggrolls and ordered another set to go. Had jerk lamb chops and ordered another set to go. Teona was our waitress and she was love ! Thank you definitely will always pop in when in town ! Need you in New York!
Hands down the freshest crab in Bmore
This place has a great menu.  The bartender was good.  The taste of the food was good but it wasn't hot(temp) at all.  A microwave wouldve been a game changer.
This is the only restaurant I’ve been to where the food is consistently delicious. Furthermore, the portion size is huge and the food is very affordable, unlike some of these other restaurants.

Waited an hour when I sent my order in via phone, then when I get there I had to wait another hour outside in the cold to get my food, manager didn’t care tried to give me cocktails with the food I waited on for so long. On top of that my food was cold.. terrible service and the food was not worth the price they charged would not recommend this restaurant.
Food was delicious and great customer service .

The food is not bad. The service for dining in is horrible. The bill will automatically include a gratuity of their choosing (I really didn't like that). If you're gonna grab a meal from there I suggest delivery or carryout.

We came all the way from Philadelphia to taste their food read the reviews trust and believe there food was everything everyone raved about the Crabcake rolls where my favorite appetizer I order the Stuff Salmon with Crabmeat Mac&Chz asparagus and Kale there seasoning of they food last in your mouth even after the food is gone Hats off to the Chefs you get a 10 rating

I have been so excited to get to this place especially since a friend of mine who recently passed spoke so highly of Papi’s. I figured I end my birthday weekend with a trip here. The service was horrible! Only one waitress named Octavia and she barley came to our table!! Never asked if we needed a refill on our drinks or anything. Then the tip was added into the bill and she didn’t deserve that, maybe that’s why she didn’t put any thought into checking on her tables cause she already knew she was getting her tip. I definitely wanna try again and hope for a better experience.

I am currently 9 months pregnant and live in philly. I drove an hour and 40 minutes after having reservations for A MONTH at 9:45pm at this restaurant. Upon getting to the restaurant I got a phone call once my vision was already inside at 9:53 and I was parking. The phone RUNG ONCE WHILE MY COUSIN AND I WERE ON THE PHONE. The staff states that they are closing early due to the pandemic, the staff at the restaurant told my cousin that they have been trying to call me all day but I have NO missed called from them besides the call from 9:53. There was no apology, no sympathy literally NOTHING! Naturally if someone had reservation for 20 mins or a month they should be contacted in advance. VERY horrible experience. I was not even offered a chance to come back the following day or anything. Extremely disappointed because I heard the food was really good and I wanted to support a black business and I don’t want to bash anybody but this is ridiculous.
Food is very good, great portion size
The food and drinks were amazing! The Crabcake Eggrolls and the Hennessy Iced Tea are worth it!
Crab cake egg rolls 😋 and believe its the surf and turf which is jerk lamb and shrimp over fries with the warhead sauce, I get this every time I go 😋😋😋
The food blew me away
Crab cake egg rolls were delicious
Food was absolutely amazing.  Everything on my plate was good. Crab Cake egg rolls are a must try
Five stars simply sums it up. Great food. Great service. Attentive owner. What more could u ask for? Black owned as well.

It was everything they said it was. Food was very good. The wait was not long for the food to be served. Pricing was a little steep . I was expecting the accommodations to be better. Hopefully this establishment will expand. Wish them all the best 👍🏾😋

Today was my first time the food was ok. I don’t know if it was because I ordered take out or not but the jerk lamb was good but a bit dry and it was packaged very sloppy it was sauce everywhere. The potatoes were a little dry not moist.
Soooo good! Make sure you try the crab egg rolls 😋
Amazing food!!! Traveled an hour from DC but in DC for a celebration weekend. Had to see what the food was like and it did NOT disappoint at all!

It took 40 minutes to get food from the appetizer menu.  Crab egg rolls, wings and warhead shrimp.  During this time, at least 10 people came in for carry out orders, which seemed to be the restaurant's priority.  I wish I had known, I would have saved myself time and aggravation.  Then it took an additional 20 minutes to get refills on 2 waters.  I felt like an afterthought as I watched everyone at the bar and surrounding tables receive their drinks and food as I waited for a refill and I only got it once my husband flagged down the gentleman behind the bar.  The food was good as usual but I didn't feel the server had enough time to take care of us.  It seemed as though he was working everyone in the restaurant alone.  And to be clear, I was there at 4pm on 10/17 and not once did I see management jump in to help, even if it had been to check on guests or bring a few drinks to me or other customers.  The service issue I experienced is ultimately a management failure.  I want to support this black owned business but this was a lot to get over.

Placed an order online, when we arrived there was no record of it. Placed an order on site, 1.5 hours later they wanted to charge an automatic 18% gratuity on a carry out order. Will not be supporting this business again!

PHENOMENAL!!! We made our reservations in September, arrived, easy check in,, we found parking, excellent customer service, and THE FOOD!!!!!! It made the trip from Leesburg, VA worth it. Everything was DELICIOUS! We had the egg rolls, lamp chops, crab cake, lobster tail, honey old bay wings, Mac n cheese, greens and surf n turf fries. It was EVERYTHING.
Great food and great service!
Thats honey Jerk Lamb was 🔥

OMG..Ive been following @papicuisine on Instagram since forever, so when he announced that he was opening a restaurant, I drove from Hampton Roads to Baltimore just for a pick up order. The food did not disappoint! I'm definitely going back  Stuffed Salmon Crab cake sandwich Jerk lamb chops, crab cake, and mac and cheese

Went for a girls dinner and the food was great. The server was a bit rude and pushy. They sat our party of 5 at a 4 seater so the table was quite uncomfortable. But the food made the trip completely worth it.
The food was excellent!! The Lamb chops are delicious!!
The food was good, I got a complimentary shot because of my birthday. That was nice of him. The service was great, we were greeted and was checked on regularly. I'll be back!
Hostess did not have her mask  on properly. Her nose was exposed.
Good atmosphere! Good service! Great food! Celebrate my husband birthday!!
So good.  Finally got to eat outside. Crab rolls are yummy and kale is the best.
Excellent service & Delicious food!
The food is excellent, and worth every penny. The best prepared lobster I’ve ever had.
A1 service! Delicious food! Good vibes! Will be returning! Best seafood in Baltimore hands down💯
Customer service was excellent!!!!
Amazing food, been rocking with Alex since the first delivery service!! Food is top 5 for me and everytime I visit I have to get some from him
It was so so wonderful I will definitely come back and tell my friends and family
Omg our girl put us on to this place and we came with her and we are hooked. You have to get the crab egg rolls they are BOMB!! I'm bringing my sis and bff here asap.
I haven't been able to hang out with my friend in months and Papi Cuisine was the perfect place to reconnect. I enjoyed myself immensely, kudos to you all!!
I came from PA to have this experience, and wasn’t disappointed.  The food was worth the trip!!!

So......when the food finally came out...its was pretty good WARM! And not to mention we in the middle of a pandemic....you bring me a Big Bottle of Ketchup that EVERYBODY Put they hands on....smh...nah I'm good...back in the house I go...
Decent.  However...they are always turning people away

Better than expected. Came for my BDay  dinner. Very nice service , Great drinks, food was delicious coming from a two proffesional Chef in the restauraunt industry we can be high in expectations hard to please over our Love&appreciation of food #cheflifestyle We loved it!...#wesupportlocal #restaurauntownersunite
It was good besides the long 25min extra wait. They could've offered a water or something
This crab meat burger was absolutely delicious!!!!  I also HIGHLY recommend the egg roll crabmeat - if you like crab meat, you will NOT be disappointed.
The food is excellent and the service is amazing! Please visit and get you some good food!  Oh and try the Margarita! You won't regret it!
Amazing lamb and mashed potatoes!!!
Food great but the service is getting worse because they can't keep up with the orders.
Service and food always on point

It is with a heavy heart that I write this review. I was beyond excited to go to Papi Cusine. I had heard great things about the crab cake egg rolls and I couldn’t wait to go. My friend and I made reservations for 9:15 on Sept 11. We arrived a at 8:35 . We didn’t mind waiting. Upon arrival my friend needed to use the restroom.  That is when I noticed a table by the bathroom. Then Lamar Jackson walked in , from that point on we were non existent. When my friend walked out of the bathroom. I told her hey that’s Lamar Jackson from the Ravens. We went outside where we saw 3 tables , I went back inside to ask of we could be seated there . It was now 8:44 we were told no that they were for other reservations. All attention went to the football star like legitimately every staff member was focused on him. Finally at 9 we were seated outside at one of the 3 remaining tables that were still open since 8:44. We sat there from 9:00-9:13 without any water or silverware and a waiter that never came back. I get it a football star comes and that takes priority, but the remaining patrons should not be ignored. Needless to say we got up and left
Wonton crab was super bomb
I ordered Honey glazed stuffed salmon online. Easy to order online, friendly customer services, quick pick up. FOOOOOOOOD WAS ABSOLUTELY AMAZING!!😋😋😋
Food is very good will go back sooner then later
Excellent all the around. Food and service. Crab Eggrolls were excellent, Crab Cake & Jerk Lamb Chops phenomenal. Will definitely be going back.
I give this place double thumbs up. The staff was helpful and kind. The place has a cool feel to it.

I wanted to treat myself for my 60th birthday. I went to papi on September around  4:30pm, the hostess was very accommodating very sweet personality.  I read some of the reviews befor going there. The crab eggroll were very delicious  and jerk lamb chops melt in mouth ans the asparagus, macaroni cheese and kale was also a very delicious the food was really good keep up the good work the staff was very polite and friendly.

I have been trying to get to Papi's for over a month and finally had the chance today.  All I can say is my 40 minute drive was worth every bit.  The only negative is online pick up time said 6:55pm but when I arrived 30 minutes later it still was not ready.

Make a reservation!!  We showed up at 1 pm on a Sunday and they were not accepting walk ins. We lucked up and got a reservation for 4:30 Pm. So we hung out in the city until it was time to go back. We sat inside. The place is not fancy. But the food and drinks make you feel like you are at a five star restaurant. We ordered the crab egg rolls. Bomb. The jerk lamb chops. Bomb. The fried lobster tail. Bomb. Greens and mashed potatoes. Bomb. One Too Henny. BOMB!!  Everything was excellent. The waitress we had was excellent as well. She made sure we were happy about everything that came out. And when we made one slight complaint, she fixed it. We didn’t even ask her to. It wasn’t a big deal. But for her, she wanted us to be more than satisfied with our experience. I HIGHLY recommend Papi Cuisine!  I’ve made two more reservations for October already.
Made a reservation on the wrong date but the staff still got me seated in a very  timely manner despite the current pandemic and the food was spectacular I would give them 6 stars if I could

Very disappointed in my meal and experience and will not return. From ordering online and having to pay the $47.34 up front and not being able to order what the menu said they had, to arriving and haviing to wait 32 mins more than my given time for my pickup, to the quality and the portion sizes, this place was the definitely not on point like I was told. Crab cake was filler with a lil crab meat. Macaroni and cheese was good, yet the portion for the money sucked and the mash potatoes, again good, portion size for the money BAD. Not returning.. only get $50 out of me once. 👎

The meats were delicious..but the sides were horrible for what you get def not worth the high price point..and then gave our order to someone else and had to wait another 20mins for our food and didnt even offer anything special for the wait..a drink a dessert or something would have been nice. ..People say support black owned business but alot of them have the worst customer service and overpriced food that isnt worth the cost

Would have been five stars. For was reheated.  Yet still the taste was amazing. I have stiffed salmon and jerkes lamb chops.  My wife has crib cake with jerk lamb chop.  The lamb chops had a perfect blend of spice and flavor.   Unfortunately we had to sit next to a woman who probably cursed more than a drunken sailor.   I'd definitely recommend this place if you're visiting the B-more area.
Food was bomb
Food was amazing, I'm going back this weekend
Food was amazing....will definitely be returning...sever Amber was great
The food was awesome. Bring your wallet! But it's super worth it

I came from Texas with a friend to visit this spot and they did not disappoint! This is a Black-owned restaurant and this location is ideal for some high foot traffic. The food was hot, fresh and VERY flavorful. Our server was phenomenal. The kale greens were good (although I wish they didn't boil down the  kale to nothing which defeats the purpose of kale). They honestly just tasted like some collards. Salmon bites and the shrimp were too good! I did provide more input on the adult slushy in a pineapple which was a new item as of 8/26/2020. Definitely make sure they put more alcohol into the mixed beverage because it can taste just like a regular slushy from 7-11. I'd highly recommend this place!

We had a really nice time visiting this restaurant for the first time. They were very accommodating when we showed up late for our reservation, my fault, which I was thankful for. The food was very good, especially the crab cake egg rolls Omg!!! I ordered the stuffed lobster, and jerk lamb which also came with 3 sides. Great experience and I can’t wait to go again!

Pros- the food is definitely as good as it looks, large portion sizes, I was full from the crab egg roll and took my order home, excellent customer service the hostess was pleasant and a great communicator and Amber our waitress had great energy, strong drinks and Clean bathroom Cons- long wait for dine in ( 1 hour past reservation time) foul odor and flies for outdoor dining and hard to find parking although that’s no fault of the establishment.
Everything was Amazing! Food and Service was great. The Crabcake Eggrolls and the lamb were my favorite!!

My party was seated 1.5 hours after our reservation time. The waitress Amber was amazing. Although the photos look mouth watering, the food quality was just ok. The shrimp were soggy and the lamb chops were too cheap of cut a for the price. The seafood egg rolls however were delicious and I liked the kale.  Bad smell while outdoor dining and no candles to keep the fly's away.  I probably wouldn't return it was a waste of $80.
Love this place

This place ALWAYS had a line and full tables every time we walked by. We only live a couple blocks away and decided to give it a try. First weekend reservation was 3 WEEKS OUT! It was totally worth the wait! We had AMAZING service and food! There was proper spacing and they seemed to do a good job cleaning. Our waitress was a superstar! She was hosting people, checking them in, and waitressing all of the outdoor seating and we still felt the service was good! We can’t wait to go back! HIGHLY RECOMMENDED!

I was truly excited about trying Papi Cuisine because the pictures look great. I typically don't like to be hard on other businesses but when you give terrible service like I experienced, I feel compelled to share my review.  Me being a decade plus business owner, I honestly expected superb service for the prices . Not only did I have to wait nearly two hours beyond the website pickup time, it was pure chaos when i arrived at the restaurant. You're basically expected to stand around outdoors waiting for your order in a large crowd of upset guests that also anticipated timely service. There was also no parking whatsoever. So be prepared to walk several blocks and stand around waiting for your order.  In terms of the food, it does not look remotely close to his internet photos. A cup of soda cost $4. While I understand businesses have to make money, the prices are quite egregious for such poor quality food. The lobster was rubbery and very difficult to chew. The Asiago mashed potatoes would have been great if they weren't so cold. The wings were overcooked as if fhey were microwaved leftovers. The fries were cold most likely because the owner does not care enough to package the fries AFTER the other items are ready to be packaged rather than bagging the rest of my order and letting it sit until the lobster is ready.  The only pleasant thing about my visit was the security officer tried his best to help the restaurant get customers their order. He seemed empathetic and sincerely friendly with customers. I was very pleased with the security guard mannerism.  Based on my horrific experience, I am convinced the owner stopped caring about guest experience and only cares about the mondy now. Clearly he makes more than enough money to offer s better expected. I lost nearly $100 on absolute poor quality food. My conscience would not allow me to take guest money and not give them a better experience.  It pains me to see the owner really does not care evident by how his order system is set up for pay in advance. In other words, he ensures he is going to be paid because he knows the probability of order cancelation when guests arrive and see the dysfunction. Me being a business owner, I read between the lines and see the owner does not seem invested in giving guests a better experience. My son is also a west coast chef so I understand a lot about upscale dining and Papi Cuisine is not it. Maybe back in the day when he was an IG entrepreneur trying to build his clientele but definitely not now. He clearly let the hype kill his integrity!
The food was AMAZING !!!!!! Dont let the wait discourage you. Its so worth it hands down!!!
The atmosphere was cool but everything taste like it had sugar in it including the mac and cheese and the mash potatoes.

Only reason I give 2 stars is because the food was okay. I had a promise time of 6:50 & was told the kitchen was backed up which is fine but not when I get told it’ll be a definite 15 more minutes but then I didn’t get my food until after 8. I then went to ask for a refund but was told “oh your food is ready, We were wondering where you were”. I NEVER received one text or call but the food was just sitting. This makes it frustrating to support black owned at times.
Great food large portions pricey but worth it. Try the fried lobster/ jerk lamb chops mac and cheese asparagus.
Food was delicious and the drinks were so worth the money.
The food was excellent...they give u an amazingexperience withgreat service and food...the waitress Amber was super nice and had AMAZING hospitality...
The food was ok well kinda good but I literally had to use the bathroom right after. I seriously had the runs .
Service was A1. Food was A1. Will be back for sure! I order the crab egg rolls and the honey jerk lamb chops with a side kale, mac n cheese and apragus.
Food is bomb!!! Customer service is excellent!!! Will be returning!!!
The food is AMAZING! Everything is very flavorful.
The food was just ok ... not worth the hour drive.
It was a wait because it was so many people trying to order but after I ate the food I forgot about the wait. Definitely worth the wait not a crumb left.

First of all for as expensive as this food is the portions were super small, the to go container wasn't even full. Second, the wait was ridiculous,  I ordered at 530pm and arrived at 645pm and was told my food wasn't ready and they would send a text when it was ready, well an hour and half later I went back to check why my order was taking so long and was told my food been ready, but I never received a call or text, they just left my $75 to go order sit there. Then finally when I got my long awaited order at 815pm it had the nerve not to be correct! I dont even want the food, never again, they do not respect your time and food is waaaaay overpriced!

Order at 1:52 pm ordered my friend food 10 min after on my same card her food was ready 15 min b4 mine i said "kool" which was 2:45 pm we waited at 2:55 pm I went to asked the hostess "how much longer"she told me "o u have to wait 20 more min" I'm confused🤔nah "I need a refund that don't even add up" drove from D.C to eat Bmore Air thanxxxx tasted like🤮

Pros: food and our server(symone) were excellent. Even though we were late(but within grace period) we were still seated. Please try the crabcake egg rolls !!! They're amazing.  I was greeted and attended to as soon as I entered. I had the warhead shrimp and mac n cheese and my guest had the jerk lamb mac n cheese mashed potatoes and kale. We loved our food. My guest also had The Hulk and she liked it.  Cons: we were inside dining and the flies unfortunately were coming in from outside and flying around our food. We were seated by a window and there were flies in the window that didn't make it back outside. With the restaurant being small inside. It was scary to see employees (2) security included walking back and forth with no mask or the mask not being worn properly and we're in the middle of a pandemic.there isn't much space between the aisle and the tables so the mask measure needs to be taken seriously.  We enjoyed ourselves and would definitely return. Hopefully these adjustments are made.

I had already been a customer but this was My first time coming down from Philly to dine at the restaurant and it was a great experience. The weather was perfect for the outdoor dining, drinks ,food and service were great! I will be going back down very soon

The restaurant in its self was so amazing! 1. The vibe was great! the music choice was my favorite which is 90s r&b. 2. The wait time for the food was about 40-50 minutes but I didn’t mind the wait because everything is freshly made 3. My wife took me to this restaurant and it was absolutely wonderful.  Food quality, presentation, ambiance were all outstanding.  I had the Honey Jerk Lamb Lollipops, Asiago Mashed Potatoes and the Ultimate Mac & Cheese...  Incredible experience.
service is always timely even when they have a full house. really nothing but good experiences here. this place has a great atmosphere. food is similar to a cafe in indianapolis i liked.

Food looks exactly how it’s pictured on the website and tastes even better. I got the honey jerk lamb, kale and mac & cheese. All of it was excellent and the service was quick and friendly.

Today I decided to try this place and I'm so glad I did! I ordered online for pickup, it was easy to navigate and efficient. I ordered the war head shrimp, stuffed salmon, honey jerk glazed lamb chops with asiago mashed potatoes, mac and cheese and asparagus and fried lobster with honey jerk glazed lamb with asiago mashed potatoes, asparagus and mac and cheese. We also added drinks for an additional $10 The Hulk and the strong island. Everything was DELICIOUS  Well worth every penny! The asparagus tastes as if it was marinaded in a lemon sauce, the salmon and lamb was seasoned to perfection. The salmon was stuffed with pure crabmeat, no filler at all. I did taste the fried lobster and the sauce as Guy would say you could put that on a flip flop and it would make it taste good. If you're on the fence, just try it! I couldn't even take pictures because I was so excited to try it! I will definitely be returning to continue to support.

THE BEST FOOD IVE EVER HAD IN BALTIMORE MD. I had a to go order as soon as I entered the restaurant I was asked by multiple workers if I had been helped. I received my food at the time promised. The atmosphere was great. The food was spectacular, crab cake was filled with lump crab and Mac n cheese  had amazing flavor. My husband and I will definitely be back. I saw multiple negative reviews but this place is still starting out their working out all the kinks as well as a pandemic. It’s worth the drive and the money!

The food was incredible!! I got the stuffed salmon and lamb chops with asiago mashed potatoes, mac n cheese and kale! When I tell you EVERYTHING was delicious! My only problem was they ran outta mac and that was such an offense! Lol but service was good and food was amazing....a must try!

This place is Grade A.....like if you love seafood and want a great atmosphere to eat it in. This is the place. I have never had mashed potatoes like that at any restaurant I been at. Since the pandemic began to leave many businesses in turmoil, my husband and I have supported minority owned businesses in Baltimore every Friday. Papi Cuisine was far most one of the best food and service experiences that we have had. Ordering online was simple and easy, and when I did have a question and needed to reach out to the restaurant they were so gracious in answering. I received a text message that my food was ready for pickup within the time window that was projected to me at checkout. When I went to pickup my food, it was delivered to my car outside of the restaurant; streamlined, simple and easy. Lastly, the food was outstanding! it was so flavorful and the portion sizes were pretty hefty which allowed me to have lunch the next day. It is so refreshing to have restaurants like this in the Fells Point community that serve authentic soul food cuisine. We will be returning for both the experience and the food.

(Yup I sure did, don't judge me judge yourself for not eating there already. Lol) I HIGHLY recommend this place. By the way they do curbside pickups and takeout. My only complaint would be they close so early (7pm). The staff was super friendly. This place is for all. Family friendly because of the outside dinning.

Sunday Brunch: Upon Arrival for a 1pm reservation, 5 minutes early, I was greeted immediately at the door and invited with smiles & welcomes from the host & server near the door. I let them know I had a table reservation & was seated right away.  I had to wait awhile for my 3 other guests to arrive but I still was constantly checked on, given a menu, and water while waiting. I also indulged in the Bottomless Mimosa. The vibe was great, smooth slow r&b music playing, was the perfect vibe for a beautiful Sunday! Let me add: The rest of the restaurant was full the entire time I was there! Once my party arrived we placed our orders. I got the Shrimp & Grits minus the crab and a side order of potatoes. I also ordered the Fried French toast!  Now listen: idk any restaurant that can compete with those shrimp & grits. The Smoked gouda Grits alone were so flavorful and creamy. The shrimp was cooked to perfection. The Fried French Toast reminded me of Funnel Cake and french toast and OMG it was soooo warm and yummy & good. Everyone at my table loved their food and had an amazing time. Not just my waitress, whose name was Amber, but everyone serving, was on it and was constantly moving.  The 1, 2 Henny punch was so light & refreshing yet packed a "punch". I appreciate a beautiful "light" cocktail, especially with dark liquor. The restaurant had a great vibe and you can tell everyone was enjoying themselves! I WOULD HIGHLY RECOMMEND YOU come out and experience YOUR OWN experience at Papi Cuisine! Don't let the miserable people on this app make you miss out! Im giving 5 Stars! Keep up the amazing work!  Also allow time to find parking, it is fells point after all.

Me leaving two stars may be a bit of a stretch but I’m not going to completely bash an establishment by my people.  A friend of mine and I patronized this place this past Saturday and had 10pm reservations.  Upon arrival we still had to wait about 20 minutes or so to be seated.  I’d say that’s not completely abnormal and the host/bartender (man who wore many hats) was pretty nice about it and explained nicely that we would be seated when I inquired about what was taking so long.  He probably could’ve offered a drink (not on the house of course) while guests are waiting past their expected reservation time.  Just a suggestion. After being seated we were greeted pretty quickly which was awesome.  Not in a friendly manner but we were acknowledged which is important.  I still couldn’t tell you if the waitress had teeth or not because she didn’t crack a smile one time while addressing us or any table as a matter of fact. We ordered drinks and appetizers.  My friend ordered some sort of margarita and I went with the old fashioned.  Then we ordered the shrimp appetizer.  Appetizer came out on time and then only one drink came out, the margarita.  I waited literally 45 minutes for the old fashioned.  This is all to be taken very literally because I am too in the service industry and am aware that timing is very important and people can also exaggerate when it comes to wait times.  I questioned this about 3x to my server and to the man who wore many hats.  He acknowledged that this wait time was ridiculous and even offered to take care of my old fashioned (which is part of doing good business).  I told him no thanks, just bring me the drink.  My friend was almost completely finished her drink at this time.  The bar wasn’t even packed so it made nooooooooo sense to me.  You aren’t supposed to serve incomplete tickets.  How do you bring a table one drink at a time and then have the other person wait 45 minutes for the other? Insane!  I still don’t understand how that happened days later lol. So we finally ordered our entrees.  My friend did the stuffed salmon and I, the strawberry pecan spinach salad.  Again my friends’s food came out first and my salad (which doesn’t have to be cooked) only assembled was nowhere to be found.  Finally the incorrect salad came out 37 minutes later.  I still can’t make sense off this because a salad does not need to be cooked and if you were picking what to send out first, the salad should’ve won hands down. They then sent me a kale salad instead of spinach.  This is when the irritation really kicked in.  I explained this is not what I ordered and they looked at me as if I should still eat it.  I sent it back.  A kale pecan salad isn’t even on the menu which I still don’t understand how some made up salad made it to the table.  Finally the correct salad came out 3 minutes later. Again, sending out incomplete tickets is not a good look and it happened twice to me in particular. The man who wore many hats checked on us and explained that they were only 10 days old.  So it made sense things were happening the way they were but I still did not understand how things for the same table were coming out at drastically different times.  It’s understood that as time progresses they’ll figure it out and hopefully get everything out on time.  The front of the house staff should actually be taught some more hospitality as well.  That can help alleviate some of the untimeliness of the food/drinks in the mean time. I’m willing to give this place about a month to get it together.  Hopefully they figure it out because they’ll have some serious troubles if they don’t.  Right now their performance is really bad for business.  I would not recommend this establishment to a friend at this very moment.  I’m FOH and none of the experience made sense to me.  Oh yea and I stand corrected, the waitress does have teeth because she was nice after I gave her a 35% tip on the check.  That’s when I figured out she had a personality at the end of the night.
